-- Sugar Awaiting Loading at Brazil’s Ports Rose 14% in Week
-- B y   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 2013-04-25T08:55:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-25/sugar-awaiting-loading-at-brazil-s-ports-rose-14-in-week.html
The amount of sugar awaiting
loading at ports in top producer  Brazil  rose 14 percent over the
past week, according to Williams Servicos Maritimos Ltda.  As many as 833,588 metric tons of sugar were waiting to be
loaded onto ships at the ports of Recife, Maceio, Paranagua and
Santos, the country’s biggest, figures e-mailed yesterday from
the Recife, Brazil-based shipping agency showed. That compares
with about 731,519 tons a week earlier.  Raw sugar for July delivery fell 0.5 percent to 17.29 cents
a pound by 4:52 a.m. on ICE Futures U.S. in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Isis Almeida in London at 
